{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Preheat oven to 220°C. Line a baking tray with baking paper, grease with olive oil and set aside.","Place garlic cloves and Parmesan cheese in mixing bowl then grate <strong><nobr>10 sec\/speed 10<\/nobr><\/strong>.","Add mozzarella and chop <strong><nobr>3 sec\/speed 4<\/nobr><\/strong>. Transfer cheese mixture to a bowl and set aside.","Place olive oil, water, plain flour, baking powder and salt in mixing bowl then knead <nobr>1 min 30 sec\/<\/nobr>. Transfer dough to a floured surface, form into a ball, divide into two pieces and with a rolling pin roll each piece into a desired shape (oval or rectangular) 3 mm thick. Place on prepared baking tray and bake for 10 minutes (220°C).","Remove flatbreads from the oven, spread ricotta cheese and cheese mixture over the dough, leaving a 2 cm border, then cover the surface of the cheeses with small pieces of Gorgonzola. Bake for further 10-15 minutes (220°C), or until the cheese is completely melted and golden. Cut hot in small pieces and serve warm or cold."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["50 g olive oil, plus extra for greasing","2 garlic cloves","50 g Parmesan cheese, cut in pieces","80 g mozzarella, cut in slices","120 g water","270 g plain flour, plus extra for dusting","1 tsp baking powder","1 tsp salt","80 g ricotta cheese","70 g Gorgonzola"]}],"id":"r143307","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-sjhJNCoMSA4\/XZWYk-r279I\/AAAAAAAAeAQ\/Y5IXk78B5IUV_HUxDqGlDnMoKCviIjn2QCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_EKLFDuSFWnC4jMFQ.png","title":"Four Cheese Sharing Flatbread","publishedAt":"2017-01-30T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"13 g","fat":"21 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"35 g","calories":"1618 kJ \/ 386 kcal"},"usefulItems":"baking tray and paper, rolling pin, oven","hintsAndTricks":["This delicious bread is perfect for sharing; serve fresh from the oven for the best flavour and texture.","To reheat, wrap the bread in greaseproof paper or baking paper, and warm in the oven at 150°C for 15 minutes.","Replace the Gorgonzola with another blue cheese such as Stilton, Dolcelatte or Cambozola."],"basicInfo":["easy","15m","40m","6 portions"]}